entries.title: A Federal Court Blocks California’s New Medical Misinformation Law
entries.description: California’s law sought to punish doctors who give patients false information about Covid-19.

entries.title: Justice Dept. Dismantles a Major Ransomware Operation
entries.description: The department said it had successfully prevented victims from having to pay $130 million in ransoms to Hive, a prolific ransomware gang, before seizing two of the group’s servers on Wednesday night.

entries.title: Stripe Hires Investment Banks to Explore Public Listing
entries.description: The payments processing start-up, one of the world’s most valuable private companies, could go public in the next year, people with knowledge of the matter said.

entries.title: University of Texas Will Offer Large-Scale Online Master’s Degree in A.I.
entries.description: Amid a boom in new tools like ChatGPT, the Austin campus plans to train thousands of students in sought-after skills in artificial intelligence.

entries.title: TikTok’s New Defense in Washington: Going on the Offense
entries.description: Keeping its head down has not paid off for the company, which now faces regulatory pressure on many fronts. So it is starting to speak out.
